The paper deals with capacity definitions for channels with side information at the receiver, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the concept of outage capacity, which is related to communication networks and reliability (cs.SI). The use of information density in deriving the capacity equations suggests a connection to network information theory (cs.NI). The examples provided in the paper involve multimedia communication and machine learning, which could fall under the categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
